  25:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   @verbatim
  26:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   ==============================================================================
  27:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****                ##### RTC and Backup Domain Operating Condition #####
  28:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   ==============================================================================
  29:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The real-time clock (RTC), the RTC backup registers, and the backup
ARM GAS  /tmp/cchPKr8B.s 			page 2


  30:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        SRAM (BKP SRAM) can be powered from the VBAT voltage when the main
  31:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        VDD supply is powered off.
  32:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        To retain the content of the RTC backup registers, BKP SRAM, and supply
  33:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        the RTC when VDD is turned off, VBAT pin can be connected to an optional
  34:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        standby voltage supplied by a battery or by another source.
  35:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  36:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] To allow the RTC operating even when the main digital supply (VDD) is turned
  37:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        off, the VBAT pin powers the following blocks:
  38:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) The RTC
  39:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) The LSE oscillator
  40:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) The BKP SRAM when the low power backup regulator is enabled
  41:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) PC13 to PC15 I/Os, plus PI8 I/O (when available)
  42:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  43:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] When the backup domain is supplied by VDD (analog switch connected to VDD),
  44:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        the following pins are available:
  45:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) PC14 and PC15 can be used as either GPIO or LSE pins
  46:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) PC13 can be used as a GPIO or as the RTC_AF1 pin
  47:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) PI8 can be used as a GPIO or as the RTC_AF2 pin
  48:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  49:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] When the backup domain is supplied by VBAT (analog switch connected to VBAT
  50:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        because VDD is not present), the following pins are available:
  51:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) PC14 and PC15 can be used as LSE pins only
  52:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) PC13 can be used as the RTC_AF1 pin
  53:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) PI8 can be used as the RTC_AF2 pin
  54:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  55:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****                    ##### Backup Domain Reset #####
  56:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   ==================================================================
  57:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The backup domain reset sets all RTC registers and the RCC_BDCR register
  58:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        to their reset values.
  59:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        The BKP SRAM is not affected by this reset. The only way to reset the BKP
  60:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        SRAM is through the Flash interface by requesting a protection level
  61:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        change from 1 to 0.
  62:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] A backup domain reset is generated when one of the following events occurs:
  63:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) Software reset, triggered by setting the BDRST bit in the
  64:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****         RCC Backup domain control register (RCC_BDCR).
  65:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) VDD or VBAT power on, if both supplies have previously been powered off.
  66:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  67:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****                    ##### Backup Domain Access #####
  68:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   ==================================================================
  69:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] After reset, the backup domain (RTC registers, RTC backup data registers
  70:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        and BKP SRAM) is protected against possible unwanted write accesses.
  71:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] To enable access to the RTC Domain and RTC registers, proceed as follows:
  72:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Enable the Power Controller (PWR) APB1 interface clock using the
  73:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****         __HAL_RCC_PWR_CLK_ENABLE() macro.
  74:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Enable access to RTC domain using the HAL_PWR_EnableBkUpAccess() function.
  75:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Select the RTC clock source using the __HAL_RCC_RTC_CONFIG() macro.
  76:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Enable RTC Clock using the __HAL_RCC_RTC_ENABLE() macro.
  77:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  78:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   ==============================================================================
  79:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****                         ##### How to use this driver #####
  80:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   ==============================================================================
  81:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
  82:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Enable the RTC domain access (see description in the section above).
  83:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Configure the RTC Prescaler (Asynchronous and Synchronous) and RTC hour
  84:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****         format using the HAL_RTC_Init() function.
  85:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  86:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *** Time and Date configuration ***
ARM GAS  /tmp/cchPKr8B.s 			page 3


  87:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   ===================================
  88:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
  89:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) To configure the RTC Calendar (Time and Date) use the HAL_RTC_SetTime()
  90:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****         and HAL_RTC_SetDate() functions.
  91:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) To read the RTC Calendar, use the HAL_RTC_GetTime() and HAL_RTC_GetDate()
  92:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****         functions.
  93:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) To manage the RTC summer or winter time change, use the following
  94:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****         functions:
  95:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****         (++) HAL_RTC_DST_Add1Hour() or HAL_RTC_DST_Sub1Hour to add or subtract
  96:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****              1 hour from the calendar time.
  97:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****         (++) HAL_RTC_DST_SetStoreOperation() or HAL_RTC_DST_ClearStoreOperation
  98:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****              to memorize whether the time change has been performed or not.
  99:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 100:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *** Alarm configuration ***
 101:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   ===========================
 102:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 103:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) To configure the RTC Alarm use the HAL_RTC_SetAlarm() function.
 104:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****         You can also configure the RTC Alarm with interrupt mode using the
 105:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****         HAL_RTC_SetAlarm_IT() function.
 106:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) To read the RTC Alarm, use the HAL_RTC_GetAlarm() function.
 107:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 108:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****                   ##### RTC and low power modes #####
 109:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   ==================================================================
 110:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The MCU can be woken up from a low power mode by an RTC alternate
 111:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        function.
 112:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The RTC alternate functions are the RTC alarms (Alarm A and Alarm B),
 113:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        RTC wakeup, RTC tamper event detection and RTC timestamp event detection.
 114:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        These RTC alternate functions can wake up the system from the Stop and
 115:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        Standby low power modes.
 116:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The system can also wake up from low power modes without depending
 117:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        on an external interrupt (Auto-wakeup mode), by using the RTC alarm
 118:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        or the RTC wakeup events.
 119:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The RTC provides a programmable time base for waking up from the
 120:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        Stop or Standby mode at regular intervals.
 121:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        Wakeup from STOP and STANDBY modes is possible only when the RTC clock
 122:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        source is LSE or LSI.
 123:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 124:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *** Callback registration ***
 125:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   =============================================
 126:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 127:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   The compilation define  USE_HAL_RTC_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
 128:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
 129:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Use Function HAL_RTC_RegisterCallback() to register an interrupt callback.
 130:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 131:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Function HAL_RTC_RegisterCallback() allows to register following callbacks:
 132:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) AlarmAEventCallback          : RTC Alarm A Event callback.
 133:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) AlarmBEventCallback          : RTC Alarm B Event callback.
 134:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) TimeStampEventCallback       : RTC Timestamp Event callback.
 135:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) WakeUpTimerEventCallback     : RTC WakeUpTimer Event callback.
 136:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Tamper1EventCallback         : RTC Tamper 1 Event callback.
 137:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Tamper2EventCallback         : RTC Tamper 2 Event callback.
 138:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback              : RTC MspInit callback.
 139:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback            : RTC MspDeInit callback.
 140:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 141:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 142:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   and a pointer to the user callback function.
 143:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
ARM GAS  /tmp/cchPKr8B.s 			page 4


 144:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Use function HAL_RTC_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
 145:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   weak function.
 146:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   HAL_RTC_UnRegisterCallback() takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 147:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   and the Callback ID.
 148:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   This function allows to reset following callbacks:
 149:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) AlarmAEventCallback          : RTC Alarm A Event callback.
 150:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) AlarmBEventCallback          : RTC Alarm B Event callback.
 151:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) TimeStampEventCallback       : RTC Timestamp Event callback.
 152:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) WakeUpTimerEventCallback     : RTC WakeUpTimer Event callback.
 153:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Tamper1EventCallback         : RTC Tamper 1 Event callback.
 154:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Tamper2EventCallback         : RTC Tamper 2 Event callback.
 155:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback              : RTC MspInit callback.
 156:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback            : RTC MspDeInit callback.
 157:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 158:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   By default, after the HAL_RTC_Init() and when the state is HAL_RTC_STATE_RESET,
 159:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions:
 160:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   examples AlarmAEventCallback(), WakeUpTimerEventCallback().
 161:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Exception done for MspInit() and MspDeInit() callbacks that are reset to the
 162:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   legacy weak function in the HAL_RTC_Init()/HAL_RTC_DeInit() only
 163:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   when these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 164:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   If not, MspInit() or MspDeInit() are not null, HAL_RTC_Init()/HAL_RTC_DeInit()
 165:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   keep and use the user MspInit()/MspDeInit() callbacks (registered beforehand).
 166:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 167:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_RTC_STATE_READY state only.
 168:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Exception done MspInit()/MspDeInit() that can be registered/unregistered
 169:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   in HAL_RTC_STATE_READY or HAL_RTC_STATE_RESET state.
 170:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Thus registered (user) MspInit()/MspDeInit() callbacks can be used during the
 171:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Init/DeInit.
 172:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   In that case first register the MspInit()/MspDeInit() user callbacks
 173:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   using HAL_RTC_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_RTC_DeInit()
 174:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   or HAL_RTC_Init() functions.
 175:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 176:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   When The compilation define USE_HAL_RTC_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 177:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   not defined, the callback registration feature is not available and all
 178:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions.
